# Laravel Pint Code Style

## When to use

- Running Laravel Pint to format PHP code (`vendor/bin/pint`)
- Checking code style without fixing (`pint --test` dry-run mode)
- Formatting only git-changed files (`pint --dirty`)
- Configuring Pint presets in `pint.json` (laravel, psr12, symfony, per)
- Customizing Pint rules: ordered imports, trailing commas, strict types, unused imports removal
- Setting up Pint for Laravel packages or Filament plugins (different include paths)
- Configuring PHPDoc alignment, return types, class attributes separation rules
- Running quality pipeline: Pint then PHPStan then Pest
- Integrating Pint in GitHub Actions CI for automated code style checks
- Adding Pint to Composer scripts (`format`, `format:test`, `format:dirty`, `quality`)
- Disabling rules inline with `@codingStandardsIgnoreStart` for exceptional cases

